description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered Nurse – Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time/Part Time Permanent contracts&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hospitals at our Oxford Road Campus/Trafford General Hospital/Wythenshawe Hospital/Manchester and Trafford Community &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Be the Nurse you want to be at MFT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join an organisation that cares for everyone. Bringing together 10 hospitals as well as community services from across Manchester, Trafford and beyond; at Manchester University NHS Foundation Trust (MFT) we pool our knowledge, skills and resources to be the best for our patients, and each other.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each and every colleague in MFT plays their part in providing outstanding care. Join us and we’ll give you every opportunity to build a hugely rewarding career with great job satisfaction in knowing your dedication and commitment has made a real difference to our patients – at a time right now that’s so important.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whatever you’re searching for in your next career move - whether you’re just graduating as a qualified nurse and looking for somewhere to support you for your exciting career ahead, whether you’re a nurse with experience looking to change your job or profession completely, whether you want to work full or part time - you’ll find real variety and fulfilment in the role of a Registered Nurse at MFT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To join us, you will be a Registered Nurse with valid registration on the appropriate part of the NMC register and have excellent written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll find working with us extremely rewarding as part of a team dedicated to providing the best possible care and experience to all our patients. You’ll be joining our Trust at an exciting time as we grow and improve our services, and we know you will make a positive contribution to its future success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support and Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support your career, we offer a wide range of development and educational initiatives that will assist you throughout your service here at MFT. We are strongly committed to all of our employees having a robust Personal Professional Development Plan throughout their career. If you are a newly qualified member of staff, you will be supported in your transition to your new role with our dedicated preceptorship program which is second to none.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interested? Apply now!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for a career as a Registered Nurse at MFT, please submit an application via the ‘apply online now’ button at the bottom of the page.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameRecruitment TeamEmail addressresourcing@mft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
